LAGOS – The Lagos State chapter of Ohanaeze Ndigbo has sworn in the State and Government Areas (LGA) executive committee (exco) members of the organisation over the weekend. The programme which was attended by the newly elected president of the socio-cultural organisation, other state executive members, local government chairmen, their excos, Ndi Eze and other prominent sons and daughters of Igbo extraction, took place in the Yaba area of Lagos State under the supervision of the electoral committee led by its chairman, Chief Oliver Akubueze, popularly called Mmiri. The swearing-in ceremony was conducted by two lawyers, Barr. Lawrence Nweke and Barr. Fabian Onwughalu in a peaceful atmosphere. Eze Chris Offia, who spoke on behalf of Ndi eze assured the newly sworn-in president, Sunday Osai of the support of Ndi eze, even as he advised him not to listen to gossip, avoid side talks, but to focus on the delivery of quality leadership. Eze Uche Dimgba, popularly called Ogbetenba, Eze Ndigbo in Ikeja appreciated everyone for the overwhelming support given to the newly sworn-in excos, and for coming out en masse to support the new leaders led by Osai.